    <!-- Splash Screen -->
    <div id="splash-screen">
      <div class="splash-content">
        <h1>Having a craving?</h1>
        <h2>Practice S.O.B.E.R.</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>S ‚Äì STOP:</strong> Pause all activity and focus on yourself</li>
          <li><strong>O ‚Äì OBSERVE:</strong> Focus your senses on the craving and take time to sit with it</li>
          <li><strong>B ‚Äì BREATHE:</strong> Take a few deep breaths or do a breathing exercise</li>
          <li><strong>E ‚Äì EXPAND:</strong> Think past the craving and consider the consequences if you indulge</li>
          <li><strong>R ‚Äì RESPOND:</strong> Address the craving like it's a person and tell it why you won't indulge today</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="container">
        <div class="header">
            <h1>30-Day Sobriety Survival Guide</h1>
            <p>A Practical Approach to Your First 30 Days of Sobriety</p>
            
            <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                <label style="font-size: 14px;">
                    <input type="checkbox" id="dark-toggle" onchange="toggleDarkMode()"> Dark Mode
                </label>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div id="intro" class="intro">
            <p>Welcome to the 30-Day Sobriety Survival Guide. Whether you're beginning your sobriety journey for the first time or looking for a fresh start, this guide provides you with a roadmap for your first month. Sobriety is more than just abstaining from substances; it's about rebuilding your life with a new sense of purpose and integrity.</p>
            <p>Each day offers actionable steps, affirmations, and tools to support your recovery. One day at a time. Let's embark on this transformation.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="progress-container">
            <div id="progress-bar" class="progress-bar" style="width: 0%">0%</div>
        </div>
        
        <div id="day-nav" class="day-nav">
            <!-- Day buttons will be generated by JS -->
        </div>
        
        <!-- Day 1 Content -->
        <div id="day-1" class="day-content active">
            <div class="week-header">Week 1: Setting the Stage</div>
            <h2>Day 1: Commitment & Mindset Shift</h2>
            <h3>Goal: Commit to your recovery with intention.</h3>
            <h3>Action Steps:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Write down your reasons for wanting sobriety. Be brutally honest.</li>
                <li>Cleanse your environment‚Äîremove triggers and substances.</li>
                <li>Reach out to a support network: a friend, group, or sponsor.</li>
                <li>Schedule a daily check-in time to reflect.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="affirmation">Affirmation: "I choose sobriety today and every day."</p>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Day 2 Content -->
        <div id="day-2" class="day-content">
            <h2>Day 2: Build Your Support Team</h2>
            <h3>Goal: Surround yourself with accountability and understanding.</h3>
            <h3>Action Steps:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Join a recovery group (online or in-person).</li>
                <li>Find an accountability partner to stay connected.</li>
                <li>Create a list of sober contacts for emergencies.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="affirmation">Affirmation: "I have a support system that helps me succeed."</p>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Day 3 Content -->
        <div id="day-3" class="day-content">
            <h2>Day 3: Establish New Routines</h2>
            <h3>Goal: Start replacing old habits with healthy routines.</h3>
            <h3>Action Steps:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Set a regular sleep schedule and stick to it.</li>
                <li>Plan and prep your meals with nutrition in mind.</li>
                <li>Incorporate gentle movement (yoga, stretching, walking).</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="affirmation">Affirmation: "Every small change I make builds a better me."</p>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Day 4 Content -->
        <div id="day-4" class="day-content">
            <h2>Day 4: Recognizing Triggers & Temptations</h2>
            <h3>Goal: Understand what causes cravings and how to handle them.</h3>
            <h3>Action Steps:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Identify triggers (places, people, feelings).</li>
                <li>Develop alternative coping strategies (breathing, talking, journaling).</li>
                <li>Practice saying "no" to temptations when they arise.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="affirmation">Affirmation: "I am in control of my responses and actions."</p>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Day 5 Content -->
        <div id="day-5" class="day-content">
            <h2>Day 5: Nutrition and Hydration</h2>
            <h3>Goal: Nourish your body to enhance mental clarity.</h3>
            <h3>Action Steps:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Eat balanced meals with lean proteins, fruits, and vegetables.</li>
                <li>Hydrate with at least 8 cups of water throughout the day.</li>
                <li>Limit caffeine and sugar intake to reduce mood swings.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="affirmation">Affirmation: "I nourish my body to support my healing."</p>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Day 6 Content -->
        <div id="day-6" class="day-content">
            <h2>Day 6: Self-Care & Stress Reduction</h2>
            <h3>Goal: Prioritize your emotional and mental well-being.</h3>
            <h3>Action Steps:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Spend 5‚Äì10 minutes meditating or practicing deep breathing.</li>
                <li>Take time for self-care (bath, walk, time in nature).</li>
                <li>Do something fun or relaxing to recharge.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="affirmation">Affirmation: "I deserve time to rest and refresh."</p>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Day 7 Content -->
        <div id="day-7" class="day-content">
            <h2>Day 7: Reflect on Your First Week</h2>
            <h3>Goal: Celebrate your progress and set new intentions.</h3>
            <h3>Action Steps:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Journal about your week: what went well, what challenged you.</li>
                <li>Celebrate 7 days of sobriety with a non-alcoholic reward.</li>
                <li>Set new goals for the coming week.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="affirmation">Affirmation: "I am proud of the progress I've made."</p>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Day 8 Content -->
        <div id="day-8" class="day-content">
            <div class="week-header">Week 2: Strengthening Your Commitment</div>
            <h2>Day 8: Managing Cravings</h2>
            <h3>Goal: Learn techniques to overcome cravings effectively.</h3>
            <h3>Action Steps:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Try the "urge surfing" technique‚Äîacknowledge the craving and let it pass.</li>
                <li>Distract yourself with a positive activity (walk, call a friend, read).</li>
                <li>Reach out to your support team when cravings strike.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="affirmation">Affirmation: "Cravings are temporary. My commitment to sobriety is permanent."</p>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Day 9 Content -->
        <div id="day-9" class="day-content">
            <h2>Day 9: Breaking Destructive Patterns</h2>
            <h3>Goal: Replace old habits with healthier alternatives.</h3>
            <h3>Action Steps:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>List 3 unhealthy habits and choose positive replacements.</li>
                <li>Start a gratitude journal‚Äîwrite 3 things you are thankful for.</li>
                <li>Create an action plan for keeping destructive habits at bay.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="affirmation">Affirmation: "I actively choose the healthy, fulfilling life I deserve."</p>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Day 10 Content -->
        <div id="day-10" class="day-content">
            <h2>Day 10: Healing Through Movement</h2>
            <h3>Goal: Use physical activity to strengthen mind and body.</h3>
            <h3>Action Steps:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Engage in a movement practice: walk, dance, stretch, or yoga.</li>
                <li>Pay attention to how your mood shifts after movement.</li>
                <li>Set a small fitness goal for the week.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="affirmation">Affirmation: "Physical movement lifts my spirit and strengthens my resolve."</p>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Day 11 Content -->
        <div id="day-11" class="day-content">
            <h2>Day 11: Emotional Awareness</h2>
            <h3>Goal: Process emotions without turning to substances.</h3>
            <h3>Action Steps:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Reflect on and journal about your emotions.</li>
                <li>Use emotional processing techniques like R.A.I.N. (Recognize, Accept, Investigate, Nurture).</li>
                <li>Talk with a trusted person about your emotional state.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="affirmation">Affirmation: "I allow myself to feel my emotions fully and without judgment."</p>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Day 12 Content -->
        <div id="day-12" class="day-content">
            <h2>Day 12: Finding Healthy Distractions</h2>
            <h3>Goal: Avoid boredom by engaging in fulfilling activities.</h3>
            <h3>Action Steps:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Pick up a hobby or explore a new interest.</li>
                <li>Do something creative (painting, writing, music).</li>
                <li>Plan a substance-free social event (book club, hiking, etc.).</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="affirmation">Affirmation: "I fill my life with enriching and joyful activities."</p>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Day 13 Content -->
        <div id="day-13" class="day-content">
            <h2>Day 13: Letting Go of Shame</h2>
            <h3>Goal: Release guilt and focus on self-forgiveness.</h3>
            <h3>Action Steps:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Write a letter forgiving yourself for past mistakes (you don't need to send it).</li>
                <li>Have a conversation about guilt with someone you trust.</li>
                <li>Remind yourself that recovery is about progress, not perfection.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="affirmation">Affirmation: "I forgive myself and embrace the future with open arms."</p>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Day 14 Content -->
        <div id="day-14" class="day-content">
            <h2>Day 14: Two-Week Reflection</h2>
            <h3>Goal: Celebrate your growth and stay committed.</h3>
            <h3>Action Steps:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Reflect on the changes in your physical, mental, and emotional state.</li>
                <li>Reward yourself for reaching 14 days sober.</li>
                <li>Set intentions for the next two weeks of recovery.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="affirmation">Affirmation: "I honor my growth and look forward to more."</p>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Day 15 Content -->
        <div id="day-15" class="day-content">
            <div class="week-header">Week 3: Deepening Your Recovery</div>
            <h2>Day 15: Healthy Socializing</h2>
            <h3>Goal: Learn to socialize without substances.</h3>
            <h3>Action Steps:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Plan a sober activity with a friend or group.</li>
                <li>Set clear boundaries with people who might not respect your sobriety.</li>
                <li>Prepare a response for when you're offered substances.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="affirmation">Affirmation: "I choose to build relationships that honor my sobriety."</p>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Day 16 Content -->
        <div id="day-16" class="day-content">
            <h2>Day 16: Managing Cravings with Mindfulness</h2>
            <h3>Goal: Learn to sit with cravings instead of reacting impulsively.</h3>
            <h3>Action Steps:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>When cravings arise, take a pause and identify the underlying emotion.</li>
                <li>Practice the "5-Minute Rule"‚Äîdelay acting on the craving for 5 minutes while distracting yourself.</li>
                <li>Engage in a healthy activity such as a walk, deep breathing, or journaling.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="affirmation">Affirmation: "Cravings may come, but I have the strength to overcome them."</p>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Day 17 Content -->
        <div id="day-17" class="day-content">
            <h2>Day 17: Process Your Emotions</h2>
            <h3>Goal: Develop emotional awareness and healthy expression.</h3>
            <h3>Action Steps:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Identify one challenging emotion you've been avoiding and write about it.</li>
                <li>Find a healthy outlet to express your emotions‚Äîart, music, talking with a friend, or exercise.</li>
                <li>Remember that healing is a process, and self-compassion is key.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="affirmation">Affirmation: "I honor my emotions and let them guide me to growth."</p>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Day 18 Content -->
        <div id="day-18" class="day-content">
            <h2>Day 18: Prioritize Sleep Hygiene</h2>
            <h3>Goal: Improve sleep quality to aid recovery.</h3>
            <h3>Action Steps:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Set a consistent bedtime and wake-up schedule.</li>
                <li>Avoid screens and stimulants such as caffeine an hour before bed.</li>
                <li>Try relaxation techniques like meditation or reading to unwind.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="affirmation">Affirmation: "Rest restores me and prepares me for the challenges ahead."</p>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Day 19 Content -->
        <div id="day-19" class="day-content">
            <h2>Day 19: Financial Wellness & Stability</h2>
            <h3>Goal: Take control of your finances as part of your recovery.</h3>
            <h3>Action Steps:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Review your spending habits and create a simple, realistic budget.</li>
                <li>Identify areas to cut back on unnecessary spending.</li>
                <li>Set a financial goal for the next 30 days (saving a set amount, paying off a bill, etc.).</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="affirmation">Affirmation: "I am building a financially stable future, one step at a time."</p>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Day 20 Content -->
        <div id="day-20" class="day-content">
            <h2>Day 20: Long-Term Vision for Sobriety</h2>
            <h3>Goal: Envision a future beyond the first 30 days of sobriety.</h3>
            <h3>Action Steps:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Write down where you want to be in 3, 6, and 12 months.</li>
                <li>Identify areas of your life you'd like to improve: health, career, relationships.</li>
                <li>Set one new goal that aligns with your vision for the future.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="affirmation">Affirmation: "I am building a future that I can be proud of, and I'm on the path to it."</p>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Day 21 Content -->
        <div id="day-21" class="day-content">
            <h2>Day 21: Celebrate Your Progress</h2>
            <h3>Goal: Take a moment to acknowledge your growth.</h3>
            <h3>Action Steps:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Reflect on how far you've come since you started. What positive changes have you made?</li>
                <li>Treat yourself to something special‚Äîa favorite activity, book, or meal.</li>
                <li>Share your journey with someone who has supported you along the way.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="affirmation">Affirmation: "I am proud of how far I've come, and I'm excited for the future ahead."</p>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Day 22 Content -->
        <div id="day-22" class="day-content">
            <div class="week-header">Week 4: Rebuilding & Thriving</div>
            <h2>Day 22: Discover Your Purpose Beyond Sobriety</h2>
            <h3>Goal: Reconnect with passions and explore new goals.</h3>
            <h3>Action Steps:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Think about activities that excite or inspire you, and make time for them.</li>
                <li>Revisit hobbies you enjoyed before addiction, or discover new ones.</li>
                <li>Consider volunteering or engaging with others who are on a similar journey.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="affirmation">Affirmation: "I am more than my past; I am building a meaningful life."</p>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Day 23 Content -->
        <div id="day-23" class="day-content">
            <h2>Day 23: Strengthen Your Boundaries</h2>
            <h3>Goal: Establish and enforce healthy boundaries to protect your sobriety.</h3>
            <h3>Action Steps:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Identify any relationships or environments that could jeopardize your recovery.</li>
                <li>Practice setting clear and firm boundaries with people who don't respect your sobriety.</li>
                <li>List safe spaces and supportive people who can help you maintain your recovery.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="affirmation">Affirmation: "I respect my boundaries, and they are vital to my well-being."</p>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Day 24 Content -->
        <div id="day-24" class="day-content">
            <h2>Day 24: Manage Stress Without Substances</h2>
            <h3>Goal: Learn new ways to cope with stress without reverting to old habits.</h3>
            <h3>Action Steps:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Identify your biggest sources of stress and create an action plan for handling them.</li>
                <li>Build a "stress relief toolkit" that includes healthy activities like deep breathing, exercise, or journaling.</li>
                <li>Practice calm responses to stressors and embrace healthier outlets.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="affirmation">Affirmation: "I am calm, collected, and in control of my stress."</p>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Day 25 Content -->
        <div id="day-25" class="day-content">
            <h2>Day 25: Repair Relationships Affected by Addiction</h2>
            <h3>Goal: Rebuild relationships with those you've hurt during your addiction.</h3>
            <h3>Action Steps:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Write an apology letter to someone you may have wronged (you don't have to send it, just express your feelings).</li>
                <li>Start small, rebuilding trust with family and close friends through consistent actions.</li>
                <li>Understand that some relationships may be beyond repair‚Äîand accept that.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="affirmation">Affirmation: "I am healing the relationships that matter most to me."</p>
        </div>
        
